      "description": "One row per model, ranked by a composite score that blends business value and cost. Formula:\n  composite = 40·atc_rate + 30/(1+1000·cost_per_conv) + 15/(1+p95_latency) + 15·quality_0_1\nWhere atc_rate is ATC events ÷ calls (so a model that converts 10% of its calls scores 4 from that term), cost_per_conv is dollars per call (Ollama≈0 → full 30 points, $0.01/call → ~15 points), p95 is seconds (sub-1s → ~15, 10s → ~1.4), and quality is the Sigil business_value_score 0-1. Practical max ≈ 100 for a free, fast, high-converting, high-quality model. Sort by any column.",
